  "text": "For \"difficult problems\", Luke [CITATION_1] concluded that a solution was more likely to be found with longer runs than with multiple shorter runs. This would produce a minimum generation that was much larger than would be obtained were the traditional approach, of terminating runs longer than 50 generations, taken.",
